<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-11-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-11-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="539" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Herbert</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Personal.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-11-04"><hi rend="italic">November 4,
                                1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Foster</hi>: If you have no objection will
                            you kindly send me copies, of Baron Ketteler’s notes of the 15th and
                            24th ultimo, relative to Samoa, quoted in your note to him of
                            yesterday.</p>
                        <p>I am called up to Kew York this evening, but shall be back again by
                            Sunday evening should you desire to see me.</p>
                        <p>Very truly, yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">M. H. Herbert.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>